Complete Data Analyst Bootcamp From Basics To Advanced
content:
The pacing was too fast, especially for technical topics like DAX and Power BI where concepts build on each other. Some videos were cut while the training is going on and there was no continuation. Sometimes the trainers incoherent. Training has files which needed to be downloaded per lecture which is quite cumbersome. A simple link to github for us to get this files at once would have been fair..

The course so far has some repetitions. Section 23 covers what already been discussed from Section 17-21. 
‚Ä¢ 	Python setup wasn‚Äôt explained, which is a major barrier ‚Äî installation is the first hurdle, and if that‚Äôs unclear, everything else collapses.
‚Ä¢ 	The instructors focused on delivering 580 plus slides instead of learning, which leaves you watching rather than understanding.
‚Ä¢ 	My expectations weren‚Äôt met, especially since I bought this course to learn, not to be overwhelmed.

If you have no prior experience in SQL, DAX this training will leave you questioning your sanity. I am currently focusing only of Power BI tutorials and projecs. 

I am unsure if this trainin will equip me with the right skills to get a jobs as a Data Analyst

content: I have an internship as a Data analyst in a very important company but didn't know a single thing about Data analysis. Honestly, you don't know how much this course taught me. And again, if sometimes I don't understand a small thing in the videos, I just make a Google search, or chat GPT, or watch a small 10-minute video and understand. Good luck to anyone who takes this course, it helps, but it is very important to learn with pleasure and not consider it as a chore

Excellent Experience highly Recommended For those who want to come in the field of Data Analysis...
